    &lt;Title&gt;Ward B6&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My dad was admitted to A&amp;amp;E with sepsis and pneumonia over a week ago. He already has advance dementia. The care in the emergency wards was excellent. 
He is now on ward B6. Often when I visit I find a staff member with my dad helping him with care or helping him to eat and drink. They have found things to help occupy him such as games and appropriate books. We have been supported as a family to make informed choices. 

The kindness compassion and care my dad has been given has been outstanding!! Competent and efficient staff. He is treated with dignity and respect at all times and the staff have gone out of their way to help him and us. The atmosphere on the ward is calm and safe. 

As a family we feel relieved to know that he is settled, safe and well looked after. Thank you so much ??&lt;/CommentText&gt;
